node.text:
Following 48 Kenyan inmates contraction of coronavirus, the government has shutdown Kericho County correctional center to avoid further spread in the country.

The decision was reached after results of COVID-19 tests conducted inmates at GK correctional center provided a surge in community transmission of the novel virus among Kenyans.

Confirming decision to seal the premises, county governor, Paul Chepkwony, through a statement made available to newsmen yesterday, stated that the decision to embark on testing in correctional centers had yielded desired result.

The Kericho County administration was said to have made several decisions to mitigate spread of the virus, part of which was suspension of visits to inmates indefinitely.

Kenya remains the second worst hit country in Eastern African behind Ethiopia with 31,763 confirmed cases, which has also prompted court services in the county to be suspended for 14 days after four law officers tested positive to the virus.

shortcode_media.accessibility_caption: Photo by Community on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: 3 people, text that says '2020 COLLOQUIUM MARKS START OF NORTHWESTERN QATAR'S ACADEMIC YEAR L 1O GULF TIMES COMMUNITY'.

node.text:
Academic publishing during a pandemic and a preview of dean Marwan M Kraidy’s strategic priorities for Northwestern Qatar were main topics that were covered in this year's colloquium, an annual event for faculty and staff. The event also highlighted the research and creative output of the university’s faculty.
Dean Kraidy outlined his four strategic priorities for this year. The first of these, he said, is to “reposition the institution as a scholarly community that is involved in the production of original knowledge and storytelling of all kinds.”

Due to the global move to online learning, a transition Kraidy believes is accelerated but not ignited by Covid-19, Northwestern Qatar is able to continue distinguishing itself in this online environment by “focusing on what we do best, taking advantage of our location, and becoming more visible as a node for creating new knowledge and new stories.”

The importance of shared governance was the subject of Kraidy’s second strategic priority, which he defined as a “self-governing faculty that abide by a set of academic values and professional norms that are then translated into processes and procedures that are both clearly spelled out and equitable.” His third priority, relates to “faculty hiring, nurturing, promotion, and retention,” which he said is “a fundamental aspect of everything that we do and has to correspond to our mission.” The fourth and final priority addressed “a programme and agenda of research where everybody becomes known for a few fundamental questions and a variety of studies around them.”
.
.
.
.

Good afternoon everyone. I hope that you all are enjoying your weekend. It’s Saturday which means that Harper’s Classroom is here to provide information on how schools are planning to practice social distancing. Here in Texas, at GPISD the district has started the school year virtually. Teachers will give online instruction, while students remain in their homes. However, students are to return back to school September 8th, 2020, but parents are given the options of either allowing their student to receive instruction full-time in person, full-time online, or part-time i person with part-time online. 

Students and teachers are required to wear masks
Students and teachers are required to social distance from another by staying 6ft/2M apart.

node.text:
Another way we are keeping things safe in the office! This air purifier is reported to achieve a 99.9999%, six log reduction, kill rate in a single air pass. The kill rate is used to describe what percentage of a given germ is killed by a particular process or disinfectant.

According to reports, when dealing with viruses, single air pass kill rates are critical to minimize the risk of cross contamination. Two key factors to consider when using technology to reduce airborne and droplet virus exposure are controlling the airflow to take the danger away from the breathing zone and purifying the air as it passes through the unit in a single air pass. While no technology is perfect we are using everything available to ensure patient safety. #covid #optometrist  #yorkville #pandemic #eyedoctor #safety #toronto #healthylifestyle #technology

node.text:
A collage of newspaper articles from the 1918 Influenza Pandemic. It’s amazing to see the similarities to our response to Covid-19. Face masks, quarantining, closed schools, quack medicine/cures, cancelled sports, and a push for vaccines were all around 102 years ago. It’s incredible to read these articles and find so many throughlines to today. Articles date from 1918-1920 from newspapers throughout the country. Full articles can be found online at https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov.

node.text:
Through our Power of Pads project, we are committed to ending Period Poverty in Western Kenya. Since the beginning of this global pandemic 71 million more people have been pushed into extreme poverty. This is having a detrimental impact on the lives of girls and women in the poorest communities. When money is so scarce that families can barely afford food, sanitary protection is all but forgotten. 

Even a small donation to our charity will go an extremely long way. We are setting up small businesses run by women who will make sanitary pads in their local area. Your money will go towards these projects and help us buy pads from these women to give to school girls for free. This not only provides these girls with much needed sanitary pads but gives money to the communities who are struggling more than ever during this pandemic. 

The link to our website is in our bio.

At LMMO we believe in the healing power of music & want to promote this virtual event! Spread the love & share with everyone you know! üéµ

What's Next,
The person I am today, Extremely Emotional yes like the¬†emotion of vulnerability is the strength I would say the willingness to show up. Emotions are hard, but trust the pain that’s why they make you strong.I meant in a very matured way that’s healing and considering my emotions  the only priority.People who wade into discomfort and to tell the truth about their stories are the real brave hearts, recently when I was locked at home for more than 6months this pandemic I caught time to myself and made full use of it in so many ways to love myself, Art therapy, Learning new skills the most productive way also made my mind very clear about the importance of Health is wealth.¬†We need the most love when we’re being most unlovable. And made myself really prepared for this new Change I read so much about Spirituality, Mythology and started concentrating only towards positivity spreading love. Life's too short to hold grudges. No matter how bad things get, the true test is how we choose to respond to the pain. We suffer, or inflict. It’s better to move forward than stay stuck in the past.¬†Self-worth comes from within We can’t control what happens to us only how it affects us and the choices we must make. To the the new Life ahead to new beginning.
